<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four paths end the same: first full draft of Brief + peer feedback note. The path is about how you spend the 30 minutes of work time before the peer feedback round.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> {{ learningIntention | safe }}
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Full work + paired peer feedback (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Spend the 30 minutes drafting all 5 sections, then paired peer feedback for 20 minutes using the protocol sheet. Default path for most students. Conferencing rotation is open the whole drafting half.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo + pairs · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Policy Aide voice-coaching on your weakest section (stretch)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Open the <a href="/ai-partners/policy-aide/">Policy Aide</a>. Paste your weakest-feeling section. Ask it to identify policy-voice problems and suggest specific edits. Document the exchange in your <a href="/foundations/ai-documentation-protocol/">AI Documentation Template</a>. Then return to peer feedback.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Self-review against the rubric (choice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Before peer feedback, score your own draft against the rubric. K/U / T/T / C each get a self-band. The point: catch your own gaps before your peer does. Especially useful if peer feedback feels exposing.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Worked-example structural analysis (practice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If you're still uncertain about policy-brief voice after the Watch, annotate the Heat Mortality demo brief: which moves do you want to copy in your own brief? Which moves are specific to that challenge? Where does the AI Doc show honest reasoning vs. invented data? Apply 2 moves to your own draft before peer feedback.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Practice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

